</div>


  <div class="comment-content">

    <div class="edit-comment-hide">
      <div class="comment-body markdown-body markdown-format js-comment-body">
          <p>Hi,</p>

<p>Thanks for IRCCloud, it's a great service, I'm a very happy customer.</p>

<p>I'm also hit by this issue so I thought I could help this been improved.</p>

<p>As far as I know, the other apps like Gmail and Facebook manage to handle cross-devices notifications correctly with a simple trick: when a notification is read somewhere else, the whole channel is marked as read and the remaining notifications pushed again.</p>

<p>It's currently the only way to do it under Android if I remember correctly.</p>

<p>Would it be possible to do that? It's getting hard to receive tons of useless Android notifications when I use the webapp 10 hours a day…</p>

<p>Thanks!</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

